Let the three consecutive integers be $x-1, x,$ and $x+1$. The sum of these integers is $27$. We write:
$$(x-1) + x + (x+1) = 27$$
To simplify, we combine the integers as $x-1,x$, and $x+1$ form an arithmetic sequence with a common difference of 2:
\begin{align*}
3x &= 27 \\
x &= \frac{27}{3}= 9
\end{align*}
The product of $x-1, x,$ and $x+1$ is:
\begin{align*}
(x-1) \times x \times (x+1) &= (9-1) \times 9 \times (9+1) \\
&= 8 \times 9 \times 10 \\
&= 720
\end{align*}
